Let $PQRS$ be a square piece of paper. $P$ is folded onto $R$ and then $Q$ is folded onto $S$. The area of the resulting figure is 9 square inches. Find the perimeter of square $PQRS$. [asy]
/* AMC8 1998 #20P */
size(1inch,1inch);
label("$P$", (0, 72), SE);
label("$Q$", (72, 72), SW);
label("$S$", (0, 0), NE);
label("$R$", (72, 0), NW);
draw((0,0)--(72,0)--(72,72)--(0,72)--cycle);
[/asy]

In the diagram, the perimeter of the rectangle is 56. What is its area?

[asy]
unitsize(1inch);

pair A, B,C,D;
A =(0,0);
B= (1,0);
D = (0,0.8);
C = B+D;
draw(A--B--C--D--A);
label("$x+2$",B/2,S);
label("$x-2$",D/2,W);
[/asy]

Below is a magic square, meaning that the sum of the numbers in each row, in each column, and in each of the $2$ main diagonals are equal. What is the value of $n$?

[asy]size(125);
for(int i = 0; i<4; ++i)
{

draw((0,i)--(3,i),linewidth(1));
}

for(int j = 0; j<4; ++j)
{

draw((j,0)--(j,3),linewidth(1));
}

label("$n-3$",(.5,.5));
label("3",(.5,1.5));
label("$n+1$",(.5,2.5));

label("$n+2$",(1.5,.5));
label("$2n-9$",(1.5,1.5));
label("$1$",(1.5,2.5));

label("$2$",(2.5,.5));
label("$n$",(2.5,1.5));
label("$n-1$",(2.5,2.5));
[/asy]

Lines $l$ and $m$ are parallel and points $A$, $B$, and $D$ are collinear. What is the value of $x$?

[asy]

unitsize(1.1 inch);

draw((0,0)--(4,0),Arrows);

draw((0,1)--(4,1),Arrows);

draw((3,2)--(1,-1),Arrows);

dot((0.3,0));
label("$m$",(0.3,0),N);

dot((0.3,1));
label("$l$",(0.3,1),N);

dot((3.7,0));

dot((3.7,1));
label("$C$",(3.7,1),N);

dot((1.2,-0.7));

dot((2.8,1.7));
label("$A$",(2.8,1.7),NW);

dot((2.34,1));
label("$B$",(2.34,1),NW);
label("$5x-8^\circ$",(2.34,1),SW);

dot((1.66,0));
label("$D$",(1.66,0),NW);
label("$143^\circ$",(1.66,0),SE);

[/asy]

The $5\times 5$ grid shown contains a collection of squares with sizes from $1\times 1$ to $5\times 5$. How many of these squares contain the black center square?

[asy]
fill((2,2)--(3,2)--(3,3)--(2,3)--cycle,gray(0.1));
for (int i=0; i<6; ++i) {
for (int j=0; j<6; ++j) {
draw((0,i)--(5,i),linewidth(0.7));
draw((j,0)--(j,5),linewidth(0.7));
};}
[/asy]

In the diagram, what is the value of $y$? [asy]
draw((5,0)--(0,0)--(0,5));
draw((.5,0)--(.5,.5)--(0,.5));
draw(Arc((0,0),1,90,360),Arrows);
label("$y^\circ$",(-1,-1),SW);
[/asy]

In the diagram below, lines $k$ and $\ell$ are parallel.  Find the measure of angle $x$ in degrees. [asy]
size(200);
pair A = dir(-22)*(0,0);
pair B = dir(-22)*(4,0);
pair C = dir(-22)*(4,2);
pair D = dir(-22)*(0,2);
pair F = dir(-22)*(0,1.3);
pair G = dir(-22)*(4,1.3);

pair X,Y;

X=A;
Y=B;
draw(1.3*X-.3*Y--1.3*Y-.3*X);

X=A;
Y=C;
draw(1.3*X-.3*Y--1.3*Y-.3*X);

X=C;
Y=B;
draw(1.3*X-.3*Y--1.3*Y-.3*X);

X=B;
Y=D;
draw(1.3*X-.3*Y--1.3*Y-.3*X);

X=G;
Y=F;
draw(1.3*X-.3*Y--1.3*Y-.3*X);

label("$\ell$",1.4*A-.4*B);
label("$k$",1.4*F-.4*G);

label("$30^\circ$",A+(.8,-.1));
label("$90^\circ$",B+(.4,.1));
label("$x$",C+(.32,.2));
[/asy]

Side $CD$ of rectangle $ABCD$ measures 12 meters, as shown. Each of the three triangles with a side along segment $CD$ is an equilateral triangle. What is the total area of the shaded regions? Express your answer in simplest radical form. [asy]
import olympiad; size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
fill((2,2*sqrt(3))--(4,0)--(6,2*sqrt(3))--cycle^^(6,2*sqrt(3))--(8,0)--(10,2*sqrt(3))--cycle,gray(0.7));
draw((0,0)--(12,0)--(12,2*sqrt(3))--(0,2*sqrt(3))--cycle);
draw((0,0)--(2,2*sqrt(3))--(4,0)--(6,2*sqrt(3))--(8,0)--(10,2*sqrt(3))--(12,0));
label("$A$",(0,2*sqrt(3)),NW); label("$B$",(12,2*sqrt(3)),NE); label("$C$",(12,0),SE); label("$D$",(0,0),SW);
draw("12 meters", (0,2*sqrt(3) + 1)--(12,2*sqrt(3) + 1),N);
[/asy]

The students in Mrs. Sawyer's class were asked to do a taste test of five kinds of candy. Each student chose one kind of candy. A bar graph of their preferences is shown.  What percent of her class chose candy E? [asy]
/* AMC8 2002 #7 Problem */
size(3.5inch, 1.5inch);
for ( int y = 0; y <= 8; y += 2 )
{

draw((0,y)--(15,y));

label(scale(0.7)*(string)y, (0,y), W);
}
label(scale(0.9)*"$A$", (1.5, 0), S);
label(scale(0.9)*"$B$", (4.5, 0), S);
label(scale(0.9)*"$C$", (7.5,0), S);
label(scale(0.9)*"$D$", (10.5, 0), S);
label(scale(0.9)*"$E$", (13.5, 0), S);
label(scale(0.7)*rotate(90)*"Number of Students", (-0.8,4), W);
label(scale(0.9)*"Kinds of candy", (7.5,-2.5));

fill((0.5,0)--(0.5,6)--(2.5,6)--(2.5,0)--cycle, red);
fill((3.5,0)--(3.5,8)--(5.5,8)--(5.5,0)--cycle, blue);
fill((6.5,0)--(6.5,4)--(8.5,4)--(8.5,0)--cycle, pink);
fill((9.5,0)--(9.5,2)--(11.5,2)--(11.5,0)--cycle, green);
fill((12.5,0)--(12.5,5)--(14.5,5)--(14.5,0)--cycle, purple);
[/asy]

On the number line shown, $AE=6$, $AB=1\frac{2}{3}$, $BC=1\frac{1}{4}$, and $DE=1\frac{1}{12}$. What is $CD$?

[asy]
unitsize(1cm);
draw((0,0)--(8,0),Arrows);
pair A,B,C,D,E;
A=(1,0); B=(8/3,0); C=(47/12,0);
D=(71/12,0); E=(7,0);
dot(A); dot(B); dot(C); dot(D); dot(E);
label("$A$",A,S);
label("$B$",B,S);
label("$C$",C,S);
label("$D$",D,S);
label("$E$",E,S);
[/asy]

For the three identical squares shown, points $A$, $B$ and $C$ are vertices, and $AB$ = $2\sqrt{5}$ cm. What is the length of $AC$, in centimeters? Express your answer in simplest radical form.

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(0,10)--(30,10)--(30,0)--cycle);
draw((10,0)--(10,10));
draw((20,0)--(20,10));
draw((0,10)--(20,0),linewidth(1));
label("$A$",(0,10),NW);
label("$B$",(20,0),S);
label("$C$",(30,0),S);
[/asy]

In the diagram, $ABC$ is a straight line.  What is the value of $x$?

[asy]
draw((-10,0)--(10,0));
draw((0,0)--(7.66,6.43));
label("$A$",(-10,0),W);
label("$B$",(0,0),S);
label("$C$",(10,0),E);
label("$x^\circ$",(0,0),NW);
label("$40^\circ$",(1.5,0),NE);
[/asy]

The trisectors of angles $B$ and $C$ of scalene triangle $ABC$ meet at points $P$ and $Q$ as shown. Angle $A$ measures 39 degrees and angle $QBP$ measures 14 degrees. What is the measure of angle $BPC$? [asy]
import olympiad; import geometry; size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
draw((0,0)--(3,0)--(4,5)--(0,0)--(2,1.5)--(3,0)--(1.7,0.5)--(0,0));
label("$P$", (1.7,0.5), S); label("$Q$", (2,1.5), N); label("$B$", (0,0),W); label("$A$", (4,5), N); label("$C$", (3,0), E);
[/asy]

Triangle $ABC$ is an isosceles right triangle with a right angle at $A$. Segments $BD$ and $BE$ trisect angle $ABC$. What is the degree measure of angle $BDE$?

[asy]draw((0,0)--(-1,0)--(-1,1)--(0,0)--cycle,linewidth(2));
draw((0,0)--dir(165)*1/cos(pi/12),linewidth(2));
draw((0,0)--dir(150)*1/cos(pi/6),linewidth(2));
draw((-1,.07)--(-.93,.07)--(-.93,0),linewidth(1));

label("A",(-1,0),SW);
label("B",(0,0),SE);
label("C",(-1,1),NW);
label("D",dir(150)*1/cos(pi/6),W);
label("E",dir(165)*1/cos(pi/12),W);
[/asy]
